column4: Microsoft's market value tops $500 billion again after 17 years
column5: Microsoft Corp's  market capitalization topped $500 billion for the first time since 2000 on Friday  after the technology giant's stock rose following another quarter of results that beat Wall Street's expectations.

column4: Microsoft profit up as demand for cloud service soars
column5: Microsoft Corp reported a 3.6 percent rise in fiscal second-quarter profit on Thursday  helped by growth in its fast-growing cloud computing business  but it saw a slight decline in margins in the unit that includes its flagship cloud platform Azure.

column4: UPDATE 3-Microsoft profit up as demand for cloud service soars
column5: Jan 26 Microsoft Corp reported a 3.6 percent rise in fiscal second-quarter profit on Thursday  helped by growth in its fast-growing cloud computing business  but it saw a slight decline in margins in the unit that includes its flagship cloud platform Azure.

column4: Tesla explains canceled order with German supplier SHW
column5: BERLIN Electric car maker Tesla Motors Inc  said it canceled a large order with Germany's SHW  because the supplier failed to meet its contractual obligations and Tesla did not want to put the production of its new Model 3 sedan at risk.
